16/07/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament unanimously approved amendments Tuesday (15 July) aimed at strengthening the fight against crime. 
According to Finance Minister Damir Kustrak, the measures envision action in three areas: tracing the financing of terrorism, smashing smuggling channels and combating money laundering. 
The law also obligates a wider range of institutions and individuals, including lawyers and public notaries, to report any suspicious transactions.
At the same session, parliament also adopted unanimously a law preventing violence during sports events. 
The measure includes severe penalties for rioters as well as event organisers who fail to guarantee sufficient security. 
(HINA, BBC - 15/07/03)
